1
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:07,838
"A prince should have
no other aim or thought -

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,629
- but war and its organization
and discipline. " - Machiavelli

3
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:19,235
Hanne Holm, political observer,
what kind of game are they playing -

4
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:23,518
- The Liberals' Lars Hesselboe
and Labour's Michael Laugesen?

5
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:27,434
- Election day is only 3 days away.
- It's a chess game.

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:31,229
The end game is all about
making things simple.

7
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:35,075
Getting a few key messages across
and making your opponent look stupid.

8
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,515
Yes.

9
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:42,956
No, we don't want to talk EU.
That's not sexy election material.

10
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:47,272
Will Denmark's next prime minister be
Laugesen or Hesselboe?

11
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:51,638
It looks like it could be
the Opposition leader, Laugesen.

12
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:56,157
He's had the initiative
throughout the election.

13
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:59,551
Hesselboe tries
to preserve things as they are -

14
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:05,238
- but Danes are hungry for change,
albeit they're unsure as to what kind.

15
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:09,598
Laugesen looks more like
an advertising guy than a politician.

16
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:15,710
- Collect autographs, do you?
- My daughter does. She loves them.

17
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:21,000
- Get Birgitte Nyborg's for her then.
- She's more into real celebrities.

18
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:24,311
- Film and rock stars...
- Are we good to go?

19
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:28,155
You're on in eight. They'll ask
why you support Laugesen -

20
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:32,518
- and you can tell them how cool
we in the Opposition are.

21
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:36,958
Conceal any signs of her
lack of sleep this past fortnight.

22
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,350
She looks fantastic.

23
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,396
HESSELBOE BEHIND

24
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,555
Christ, Lars.

25
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:40,116
- You're still on these?
- It's the election.

26
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:43,670
I'm surprised you have a heart.

27
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:50,434
Hi. Let's do it out here.
In front of Parliament.

28
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:53,751
Ask me about asylum seekers only,
got it?

29
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:57,629
As always in Danish politics,
the fight is over the center.

30
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:01,395
The coalition with the centrist
Moderates benefits the Opposition.

31
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:06,839
Our next guest is Moderate leader,
Birgitte Nyborg Christensen. Welcome.

32
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,434
Kasper.

33
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:13,317
Oh, it's just business as usual.

34
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,517
We need to break the old patterns...

35
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:19,717
Zoom out on Katrine, 3.

36
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:25,793
- Where's Parliament?
- On 4.

37
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:30,272
- 4?
- 4, yes. Yes, get her shoulder, 3.

38
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:37,753
- Is that a live feed?
- Yes.

39
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:41,390
- Cue it up.
- We're running out of time.

40
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,632
So drop a few features. Cue it up.

41
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:48,713
Katrine, have Nyborg comment on
this interview just in with Laugesen.

42
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:53,271
At 11 she has a debate meeting
with some Labour hillbilly.

43
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:57,831
Overby, right.
She's gonna wipe the floor with him.

44
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,472
Do you share your coalition partner's
vision for the future of Denmark?

45
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:06,757
Yes, it's the very foundation
of our coalition.

46
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:11,038
I'd like your comments on this fresh
interview with Michael Laugesen.

47
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,273
Many Danes are worried about
the rising number of asylum seekers -

48
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:18,955
- in the wake of the Iraq war.
Let me make one thing clear:

49
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:22,112
Most of them will be sent back home -

50
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:26,034
- and until then
they'll be confined in refugee camps.

51
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,760
But you said they could work...

52
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:32,310
Look, we don't want them
taking Danish jobs.

53
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:39,352
We can't have employment hampered
by refugees already burdening us.

54
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:44,230
- So, will they be allowed to work?
- No, they won't be allowed to work.

55
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,154
Birgitte Nyborg, isn't Laugesen
going back on a deal here?

56
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:54,350
- It might be taken out of context.
- No, he's replying to a question.

57
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,750
Katrine, pile on the pressure.

58
00:04:56,920 --> 00:05:01,710
The issue here is immigration policy,
a key issue to you and the Moderates.

59
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:05,668
If Laugesen goes back on his word, do
you still prefer him as prime minister?

60
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:08,877
Yes, of course we do.

61
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:15,479
- I need to find out if Laugesen...
- Dodge! Change the subject.

62
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,791
- Dodge!
- Laugesen is going back on his word.

63
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:22,396
Do you still support Laugesen,
yes or no?

64
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,039
Yes.

65
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:31,596
No. If that's Labour's new policy,
Laugesen no longer has our support.

66
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,955
Thank you, Birgitte Nyborg.

67
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,998
They're changing their policy
this late!

68
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:40,675
The train scandal continues...

69
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:41,150
GOVERNMENT
Episode 1

70
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:08,191
You own welfare and tax reform.

71
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,237
Jesus Christ!

72
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:29,279
It was in the news one minute ago.
Birgitte Nyborg rejects Laugesen.

73
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:43,675
- They won't let me buy anything.
- Honey, it's not...

74
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:47,913
Help me. My card keeps bouncing,
and I'm not leaving without that bag.

75
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:51,834
- I'm talking to my husband, damn it!
- Where are you?

76
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:56,198
Mulberry near Burlington Arcade.

77
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:59,557
It's all because you always desert me.

78
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:05,590
- You bastard!
- Honey, get a cab back to the hotel.

79
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:10,629
- I'm not leaving without that bag.
- Calm down, honey.

80
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:15,635
I deserve to have it good,
do you hear?

81
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:29,113
- I'll try to get a plane later.
- See you back home.

82
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:05,959
I'll handle this on my own.

83
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:10,875
- What's up, honey?
- Fucking store. I want this stuff.

84
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,749
- Let's come back later.
- No!

85
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:20,313
- You've bought for 12,000 dollars.
- And? I take so much crap from you.

86
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:23,870
How about giving something back?

87
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:28,470
- Lisbeth, please...
- Why can't you be nice to me?

88
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:39,474
- I forgot my wallet.
- Oh, shut up.

89
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:01,756
- Call that good journalism?
- Yes.

90
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:06,232
Birgitte Nyborg's spin doctor is
gonna have your ass.

91
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:11,076
- It comes with the job, Ulrik.
- Sure it does. Good luck.

92
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:19,996
You broke our deal. We demanded
to know your questions and angle.

93
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:24,597
- Ever heard of the free press?
- You know how this shit works.

94
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:29,072
- We're in the news business, Kasper.
- So, when can I see you?

95
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:31,708
- Soon.
- You never call.

96
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:34,872
Are you seeing someone?

97
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:38,112
- Is Birgitte Nyborg angry?
- No, she's a pro.

98
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:42,990
You don't pounce on your interviewee
three days before the election.

99
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:47,950
- Go for your prizes some other time.
- I'm sorry you feel that way.

100
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,908
We're here to cover the election,
not to support you.

101
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:01,552
Changing our policy three days before
the election calls for a new strategy.

102
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:07,477
I have that debate meeting in
20 minutes. We'll meet this afternoon.

103
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:11,474
- Is the car waiting?
- Yes. I'll talk to their head of news.

104
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:15,519
Katrine Fønsmark won't interview you
ever again.

105
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,315
Torben, Kasper Juhl speaking.

106
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:36,871
- Why can't we meet at the office?
- Something happened in London.

107
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:40,476
- Yes, you forgot this.
- I'm talking about Lisbeth.

108
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:44,349
- Popping pills again?
- She bought for 12,000 dollars.

109
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:48,911
Her Visa card bounced, and I was
afraid someone might see her.

110
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:54,279
She was about to make a scene,
so I panicked.

111
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:59,833
I only had my official Eurocard.
I know it was stupid.

112
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:03,834
Maybe you never should have brought
Lisbeth along to London.

113
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,151
I'll take these
and settle it with the Ministry.

114
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:10,596
You made a Party purchase
and didn't bring the right card.

115
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:14,548
It won't be charged to your account
for another two weeks.

116
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,109
We're sticking to the plan.

117
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:22,035
The Moderates will come crawling,
after Nyborg rejected the Opposition.

118
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,158
- She's rejected us so far.
- She needs new friends.

119
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:30,599
Besides, we owe her one. She just
gave you four more years, Lars.

120
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:34,912
See you.
I'm staying in town tonight to work.

121
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:50,671
How bold of you to change your policy
three days before the election.

122
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:53,479
I thought Nyborg was a smart girl.

123
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:57,110
How about a serious talk
when we've got a handle on things?

124
00:12:57,280 --> 00:13:00,158
Why would we want to talk to you?

125
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:04,359
You need an alternative to the
Freedom Party to ensure your majority.

126
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,988
We need to talk immigrants and taxes.

127
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:12,393
We need 90 seats, and right now
you look like shit in the polls.

128
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:18,351
Round up your party for a charm
offensive this weekend. Call me.

129
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:21,273
And have fun.

130
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:30,072
- You should have dodged the bullet.
- Like we always do in this party?

131
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:33,789
- Like professional politicians do.
- See you.

132
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:37,191
- The Party is gonna have your ass.
- Nope.

133
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:42,150
I just talked to Nørgaard, Gjervig
and Lindholm. They're all behind you.

134
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:47,474
- This was bound to happen anyway.
- Laugesen isn't our natural choice.

135
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:52,191
Natural? We're not picking members
for the softball team here.

136
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:56,751
We're running for office here.
Did you see the latest polls?

137
00:13:56,920 --> 00:14:01,072
- There's more to politics than polls.
- Not three days before an election.

138
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:04,471
We listen to the polls,
but they don't dictate our policy.

139
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:08,792
I know the Liberals want to talk to us.

140
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:12,919
I think we can keep the Freedom Party
out of power.

141
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:18,950
You scold her for leaving Labour. Now
you want her in bed with the Right?

142
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:24,478
- I have a birthday party to go to.
- Are you taking this seriously?

143
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,152
I work 16 hours a day,
or haven't you noticed?

144
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:34,279
I'm not going to make ouvertures
to the Right until after the election.

145
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:38,797
That is the Moderate Party's policy
as decided by me, their leader.

146
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:43,829
It's Saturday. I promised my children
the next four hours three weeks ago.

147
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:51,040
Never let your children down, Kasper,
because they grow up to be voters.

148
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,876
Hi.

149
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:25,994
- I missed you today.
- Boy, you look fantastic.

150
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:30,233
It's fake. I'm still in makeup
from this morning's show.

151
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:39,910
It was great! Just think, a politician
changed her policy on live TV.

152
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:44,437
- It was crazy.
- This is for you.

153
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:50,675
- Thanks. What is it?
- They said it's 150 years old.

154
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,392
- I bought it in London this morning.
- I thought you were too busy for that.

155
00:15:56,560 --> 00:16:02,954
We were, till the Prime Minister's wife
popped a handful of tranquilizers.

156
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:06,635
- I thought we didn't talk about that.
- We don't.

157
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:11,714
If we do, I have a lot of questions.

158
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:15,190
I want to be with you all the time.

159
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:18,511
But...

160
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:23,630
- But?
- I'm lying to Nina and the kids.

161
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:31,392
- I have to make a choice.
- So does everyone in three days.

162
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,992
- I've made my choice.
- Was that a farewell gift?

163
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:42,359
No. I'm going to leave Nina.
I want to be with you.

164
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:48,914
All the time. Officially. No bullshit.
Get it?

165
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:26,238
- Is that ice skating thing tomorrow?
- Yes. Dad's taking me, right?

166
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:29,631
- Yes.
- I'm going to practice my piano.

167
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:34,157
Put on your headphones,
so you won't wake Magnus.

168
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:41,428
Hasn't she been playing
"Let it Be" for two months now?

169
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,070
How's it coming along?

170
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:50,519
I don't see an international career
in the cards for her.

171
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:55,231
Honey, you really buy
too much dessert.

172
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:59,313
And pastry for breakfast. I know it's
for the kids, but I end up eating it.

173
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:02,711
You always gain weight
during an election.

174
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:06,156
Hey, you!
Did I ask for honesty here?

175
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:10,871
"Voluptuous Birgitte Nyborg
in an elegant black dress. "

176
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:14,589
- They wrote that after that premier.
- So?

177
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:19,117
Black slims.
Black is sophisticated and sexy.

178
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:23,432
- Voluptuous in black is bad.
- Look, honey.

179
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:28,469
You get the most fantastic ass
during an election -

180
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:33,236
- and I try to live with that
in my own slightly primitive way.

181
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:36,517
Keep going.

182
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:41,435
I can't. You've cut off
the blood supply to my legs.

183
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:48,999
You used to be so funny.
You're losing your touch.

184
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:02,233
Michael Laugesen wants me to drink
champagne with Labour tomorrow.

185
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:07,713
When I was young, champagne
and Labour ruled each other out.

186
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:14,513
- Should I go?
- How tactical do you want to be?

187
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:19,518
I'm trying to salvage the remains,
but I don't want it to look that way.

188
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:25,357
Go. Make him retreat. Tell your voters
you'd rather topple the government -

189
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:29,593
- than sacrifice the Opposition
over a key issue.

190
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:35,232
- That's gonna take some swallowing.
- Wash it down with some ice cream.

191
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:40,355
- But you are funny.
- A scream.

192
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:49,194
Kasper, my usually smart ex,
asked me if I was seeing someone.

193
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:55,358
I just ignored the question.
I'm turning into a fantastic liar.

194
00:19:55,520 --> 00:20:00,435
My mom doesn't even know you exist.
She will soon, though.

195
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:06,118
"Meet my new boyfriend, Mom.
13 years older, married with kids. "

196
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:14,316
I've never been happier.
I just thought you should know.

197
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:19,474
Meanie! If you're asleep, you're not
getting any sex the next month.

198
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,350
Ole.

199
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,837
Ole... look at me.

200
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:38,156
Ole, say something!

201
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:42,199
Come on, damn it!
It's not funny, okay?

202
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:48,832
Svend Åge Saltum, the Freedom Party
applauds Laugesen's remarks.

203
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:56,111
It's no secret that Labour needs to get
back in touch with their voters -

204
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:58,589
- many of whom are switching to us.

205
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:02,878
- Taking notes, Kasper?
- Good evening, Svend Åge.

206
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:06,555
No, your rhetoric is
crystal clear as always.

207
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:09,792
What is it you do, Kasper?

208
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:14,033
My constituency wants me
to hire a guy like you.

209
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:21,356
But I don't quite know what you do
to earn your no doubt grand salary.

210
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:26,150
What do they call you again?
Spin doctor, huh?

211
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:29,471
- Yes.
- But who's sick, Kasper?

212
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,469
Oh, excuse me.

213
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,873
- Kasper Juhl.
- Kasper...

214
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:44,113
What did people like you do
before they invented the cell phone?

215
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:48,034
- Katrine, what's up?
- I think he's dead.

216
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:52,671
- Take a breath. What's up?
- I don't know what to do.

217
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:56,071
He's just lying there
with his eyes open.

218
00:21:56,240 --> 00:22:00,199
- I've tried everything.
- Where are you?

219
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:03,750
Tell me where you are,
and I'll be right over.

220
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,319
20 Bredgade, please.

221
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:24,352
He just went and died.
I guess he must have been sick.

222
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:37,958
So the guy you kept a secret from me
was the Prime Minister's PR advisor?

