women voters: Size doesn't count.

448
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:05,034
Welcome to the Final Debate, 2010.

449
00:43:13,080 --> 00:43:17,312
This is it. It's time for the closing
remarks from each party leader.

450
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:20,916
We'll begin
with Anne Sofie Lindenkrone.

451
00:43:21,080 --> 00:43:27,918
I'm ashamed to be a Dane in this
selfish nation Hesselboe has created.

452
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:31,311
- Amir Diwan is on camera 3.
- Is Diwan with a W?

453
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:32,913
Yes.

454
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:38,757
A vote for us is a vote for a green,
financially sound Denmark.

455
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:43,118
Denmark needs a modern,
well-trained military...

456
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:44,679
Hesselboe on 3.

457
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:51,678
Individual freedom and initiative
is what keeps Denmark going.

458
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:56,197
Can we still take care
of our senior citizens -

459
00:43:56,360 --> 00:44:01,559
- when we have to take in criminal
immigrants who travel 4,000 miles...

460
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:07,078
Next up is Birgitte Nyborg.
Roll 3.

461
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:09,959
Thank you, Svend Åge Saltum.

462
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:14,398
Last but one is Birgitte Nyborg.
The floor is yours.

463
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:19,757
All of us here have become
ever so professional.

464
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:24,675
We know every question, because
we check them off with the reporters.

465
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:30,676
She's improvising. Katrine, that isn't
her speech. She's going impro.

466
00:44:30,840 --> 00:44:34,276
All this decides our actions.

467
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:41,039
I'm shocking my spin doctor right now
by not sticking to my speech.

468
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:45,352
I upset him by not wearing
the right clothes either.

469
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:50,071
The trouble is
I've gotten a bit too fat for them.

470
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:57,989
Zoom out and let's see the dress.
Great, stay with that.

471
00:44:58,160 --> 00:45:01,357
I believe we must
own up to our mistakes -

472
00:45:01,520 --> 00:45:04,557
- and admit it when
there's something we don't know.

473
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:07,188
I became a politician -

474
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:12,354
- because I once held strong views on
how this world should be. I still do.

475
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:16,991
I believe we're losing
what keeps Denmark together.

476
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:22,518
I believe, unlike the Freedom Party,
we do live in a multiethnic society -

477
00:45:22,680 --> 00:45:25,797
- so it's a waste of time
to discuss how to avoid it.

478
00:45:25,960 --> 00:45:30,909
I believe it's a myth that we're all
equal and share equal possibilities.

479
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:35,517
These past seven years have seen
the gap widen between poor and rich.

480
00:45:35,680 --> 00:45:40,310
The Prime Minister will say: "Oh, but
everyone is a master of his own fate. "

481
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:45,474
But to believe that the free market is
the best cure for social inequality -

482
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:51,590
- is like saying cars will cure the
climate crisis. It's not good enough.

483
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:54,797
If we're to create a new Denmark
together -

484
00:45:54,960 --> 00:46:00,990
- we have to invent a new way
of communicating and doing politics.

485
00:46:01,160 --> 00:46:06,757
Words like socialism, liberalism
and solidarity just might be words -

486
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:10,959
- describing the world of yesterday
and not the world of tomorrow.

487
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:16,877
A modern world is manifold,
and so must our democracy be.

488
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:22,353
A vote for the Moderates tomorrow is
a vote for a new Denmark. Thank you.

489
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:31,278
Christ! Nyborg has really got it tonight,
hasn't she?

490
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:36,468
That's your mom.
You can be proud of her.

491
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:41,031
- So, Michael Laugesen, top that.
- You bet I will.

492
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:47,878
I prepared a speech like, well, almost
everyone else. But I can't deliver it.

493
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:53,672
Not after having seen proof of the
Prime Minister's arrogance of power.

494
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:58,038
For seven years, he's been preaching
financial responsibility to the voters.

495
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:01,431
How does that add up, Hesselboe -

496
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:06,628
- when you let the state finance
your own overconsumption?

497
00:47:06,800 --> 00:47:10,554
- What are you talking about?
- This is a receipt.

498
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:17,637
You billed the state 12,000 dollars
for gifts to your wife, Prime Minister.

499
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:21,395
- Christ!
- Zoom in on the receipts.

500
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:25,030
What's going on? Keep going.

501
00:47:25,200 --> 00:47:29,637
- 12,000 dollars, Lars Hesselboe!
- Don't the rules apply to us all?

502
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:35,158
- Let the Prime Minister reply.
- Katrine, over to him.

503
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:38,756
Let's give Lars Hesselboe
a chance to reply.

504
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:45,268
I don't know what receipts he's got,
but this is not the place to air them.

505
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:49,228
- Is this your signature, Hesselboe?
- Stop that!

506
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:54,679
I won't stand for
your fabricated accusations... No!

507
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:59,197
Talk to my lawyer.
I'm leaving this debate now.

508
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:04,750
- If that isn't an admittance...
- Follow him out.

509
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:08,117
All the way out.
Screw aestethics!

510
00:48:08,280 --> 00:48:13,673
Thank you, Michael Laugesen.
The debate is over. Thank you.

511
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:19,676
This debate came to a somewhat
surprising end. Tune in later for more.

512
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:22,877
I wish you all a good election.

513
00:48:23,040 --> 00:48:26,953
- We're off.
- Alright! Jesus Christ!

514
00:48:27,120 --> 00:48:30,635
That was fucking great TV,
girls and boys.

515
00:48:32,800 --> 00:48:37,874
You were great. I'm sure my daughter
wants your autograph now. Later?

516
00:48:38,040 --> 00:48:40,554
Sure.

517
00:48:45,160 --> 00:48:49,517
Where did Laugesen get
that information?

518
00:48:49,680 --> 00:48:54,993
Come in at nine tomorrow
and clear your desk.

519
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:13,879
Bye-bye.

520
00:49:14,680 --> 00:49:17,399
Today, the Danes will decide -

521
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:21,109
- who is going to rule Denmark
the next four years.

522
00:49:21,280 --> 00:49:26,149
The polls aren't painting a clear
picture after yesterday's debate -

523
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:30,598
- dubbed the most chaotic ever.

524
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:37,030
THE PRIME MINISTER
STANDS ACCUSED

525
00:49:51,880 --> 00:49:55,270
We'd have made a good pair
in the long run.

526
00:49:55,440 --> 00:50:00,116
Spare me the emotions.
That's my field.

527
00:50:00,280 --> 00:50:02,430
My keys.

528
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:10,158
And your phone. The computer, and
the campaign documents are there.

529
00:50:10,320 --> 00:50:15,997
I told security I'd take your ID card
before you leave Parliament.

530
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:24,154
Thank you.

531
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:45,679
Birgitte! The Labour top brass are
washing their hands of Laugesen.

532
00:50:47,440 --> 00:50:53,390
The dramatic debate is sending shock
waves throughout the Labour Party.

533
00:50:53,560 --> 00:50:56,757
Respected former leader
Hardy Eriksen -

534
00:50:56,920 --> 00:51:02,472
- calls Laugesen's behaviour
at the debate a disgrace.

535
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:07,589
"I no longer support Laugesen's
leadership," Hardy Eriksen says.

536
00:51:10,520 --> 00:51:14,433
This can go any which way.

537
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:17,558
We'd better look sharp tonight.

538
00:51:33,920 --> 00:51:37,913
According to the first exit polls -

539
00:51:38,080 --> 00:51:43,438
- the Moderates are tonight's winners
with over eight seats in Parliament.

540
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:47,559
- Mom, you're eight points ahead.
- Seats, you moron.

541
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:53,829
- Don't tease.
- It's true. It just came in.

542
00:51:56,280 --> 00:52:00,671
I hate this.
I hate this, I hate this, I hate this.

543
00:52:00,840 --> 00:52:04,833
- Not now, Phillip. I'm in hell.
- Birgitte.

544
00:52:19,280 --> 00:52:25,310
I made the dry cleaner buy you a new
one, seeing as he shrunk the old one.

545
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:31,711
I love you.

546
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:36,396
Things are heating up.
We expect Labour leader...

547
00:52:36,560 --> 00:52:40,633
We're still waiting
for the key figures...

548
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:44,076
Are you waiting for me, or...?

549
00:52:44,840 --> 00:52:49,118
- No, wait. Let him go in first.
- Why?

550
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:53,159
Mom deserves to go on TV too.

551
00:52:55,160 --> 00:52:59,756
Prime Minister Hesselboe just arrived.
How do you feel about the result?

552
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:05,358
I'm shocked that this misunderstanding
had such grave political implications.

553
00:53:05,520 --> 00:53:08,717
Your lawyer hasn't
repudiated the claim -

554
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:12,475
- that your wife billed the state
12,000 dollars for clothes.

555
00:53:12,640 --> 00:53:18,556
- I assure you, there's nothing in it.
- Are you still Prime Minister?

556
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:21,670
Okay.

557
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:28,919
Hesselboe hasn't been able
to rebuff my evidence.

558
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:32,311
He committed fraud and must pay.
I don't regret a thing.

559
00:53:36,160 --> 00:53:39,948
I'd like to direct your attention
to my wife's dress.

560
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:44,671
Ten years old,
63 dollars at the local market.

561
00:53:52,040 --> 00:53:57,273
Here comes one of tonight's winners,
Moderate Leader, Birgitte Nyborg.

562
00:54:02,760 --> 00:54:05,558
Remember this, honey.

563
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:13,154
The Moderate Party is sky-rocketing.
They've gained ten more seats.

564
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:19,157
This is insane!
We've gained ten seats, Birgitte.

565
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:23,313
What if they're useless,
because Hesselboe has enough?

566
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:28,031
He lost 12 seats.
He has to resign. The door is open!

567
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:31,317
- We're going home.
- I want to see the result.

568
00:54:31,480 --> 00:54:35,519
You look beat.
Just look at your brother.

569
00:54:35,680 --> 00:54:39,878
- Are you okay with this?
- Sure. You look like a statesman!

570
00:54:40,040 --> 00:54:42,873
Come along, kids.

571
00:54:44,560 --> 00:54:49,111
And the success continues.
Two more seats...

572
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:55,718
We now have the national result.

573
00:54:55,880 --> 00:55:00,271
Tonight, Denmark has seen
a landslide victory.

574
00:55:00,440 --> 00:55:05,230
The two major opponents, Laugesen
and Hesselboe, are the two losers.

575
00:55:05,400 --> 00:55:08,790
The winner is without a doubt
the Moderate Party.

576
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:11,679
15 seats. I just don't get it.

577
00:55:11,840 --> 00:55:17,392
You hit the zeitgeist. This is
the beginning of something new.

578
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:22,350
Now, thank them and lead them,
because they want to be led by you.

579
00:55:22,520 --> 00:55:27,355
- What if I don't know how?
- You'll learn it along the way.

580
00:55:41,360 --> 00:55:44,750
We've come a long way.

581
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:58,116
Commentators say the voters voted
against Labour and the Liberals -

582
00:55:58,280 --> 00:56:02,239
- because of the showdown
between Laugesen and Hesselboe -

583
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:06,473
- and that void was filled
by Birgitte Nyborg...

584
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:16,358
Coming? Torben is asking for you.
He's about to make a speech.

585
00:56:16,520 --> 00:56:18,875
I'll be right in.

586
00:56:24,480 --> 00:56:28,439
Katrine, come on.
I'm singing your praise.

587
00:56:32,080 --> 00:56:34,071
What's up?

588
00:56:36,840 --> 00:56:39,035
There, there...

589
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:50,151
DENMARK ELECTED FOR DECENCY

590
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:52,072
Thanks.

591
00:57:06,160 --> 00:57:08,037
Hi.

592
00:57:17,760 --> 00:57:21,753
- I didn't buy pastry.
- They want me for prime minister.

593
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:36,998
Subtitles: Helle Schou Kristiansen
Dansk Video Tekst

